		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I have an NES controller port like the one pictures here (minus the wires):<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.battlenerds.com/wp-content/uploads/bpfattach/img_1347.jpg">http://www.battlenerds.com/wp-content/u ... g_1347.jpg</a><!-- m --><br /><br />I'm trying to wire it to my BASIC Stamp microcontroller to control a servo, and the standard jumper wires don't fit the pins.  I'm pretty new to electronics, so I'm not sure what else to try.  I know that you can buy a circuit board with the controller mounted and wired, but I'd like to do it myself if possible.<br /><br />Any help is appreciated.<br /><br />Thanks,<br /><br />KKat

		

