		<td><b>Re: Jumper for NES Controller Port</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Do you mean the pins inside the jack, that would normally connect to a gamepad? They're slightly larger than normal 1/10&quot; header, more comparable to the pins in a DE9 (&quot;serial&quot;) connector. (They're about 1mm in diameter)<br /><br />Or do you mean the ones on the other side, that in the picture have been soldered to the PCB? That's 2mm spacing, probably the exact same size as the old PATA laptop hard drive pins.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


